<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1CFF85FF0AEB04FEDBFB4D" blockId="28.[178,1085,1093,1174]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) is composed of the adjectives parvus (small) and incisus (incised). It alludes to the relatively small posterior incision of the male sternite VIII.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A1CFF87FF0AEBE4FEF9FDFD" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="1163" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1CFF85FF0AEBE4FDE7FACB" blockId="28.[178,1085,1189,1299]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">
Description: Body length 4.0- 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A1CFF85FD87EBE4FD24FB62" box="[575,658,1189,1210]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A1CFF85FCD1EBE4FC52FB62" box="[873,996,1189,1211]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161" unit="mm" value="2.4" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.3">2.3-2.5 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head dark-brown to black; pronotum brown to dark-brown; elytra brown; abdomen brown to dark-brown, with the posterior margins of the segments yellowish to yellowishbrown; legs yellowish; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1CFF85FF0AEA63FED2FA75" blockId="28.[178,1085,1314,1453]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">
Head (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1CFF85FF43EA63FEFCFAE0" box="[251,330,1314,1336]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, 1.06-1.09 times as broad as long, lateral margins behind eyes subparallel in dorsal view; punctation dense and fine; interstices with shallow microreticulation, glossy (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1CFF85FE4EEA1CFDF1FAAB" box="[502,583,1373,1395]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
). Eyes large, noticeably longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antennae approximately 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A1CFF85FD17EA3BFCB6FA57" box="[687,768,1402,1423]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long; preapical antennomeres distinctly oblong.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1CFF87FF0AEAFCFBB0FEF3" blockId="28.[178,1085,1468,1578]" lastBlockId="30.[178,1086,219,299]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="1163" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1CFF85FE9CEAFDFED8FA0A" box="[292,366,1468,1490]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad and as broad as head; anterior angles sharply, posterior angles weakly marked; lateral margins weakly converging posteriad in dorsal view; midline with pronounced impunctate band; punctation dense and fine, slightly more distinct than that of head; interstices without microsculpture (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1CFF85FC14E955FC4FF9F2" box="[940,1017,1556,1578]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1161">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
). Elytra (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1EFF87FF47EF9AFEFFFF28" box="[255,329,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as long as pronotum; punctation very dense and fine; interstices without microsculpture. Hind wings present. Protarsomeres I-IV weakly dilated. Metatarsomere I approximately as long as the combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF47BB8B3A1DFF84FF0AEA9DFC31F9EE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162" startId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" targetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1DFF84FF0AEA9DFC31F9EE" blockId="29.[178,1085,1500,1590]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FF0AEA9DFEA0FA29" bold="true" box="[178,278,1500,1522]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">Figs 76-84</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A1DFF84FE9BEA9DFDD9FA29" authority="CAMERON" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1936" box="[291,623,1500,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preangerana">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FE9BEA9DFDB1FA2A" box="[291,519,1500,1522]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">Lithocharis preangerana</emphasis>
CAMERON
</taxonomicName>
, holotype (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FD60EA9DFD59FA29" bold="true" box="[728,751,1500,1521]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">76</emphasis>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A1DFF84FC93EA9CFC12FA2A" authority="Assing, 2015" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[811,932,1501,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvincisa" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FC93EA9CFC12FA2A" box="[811,932,1501,1522]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">L. parvincisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27F8A6A3A1DFF84FC12EA9CFC5BFA2A" box="[938,1005,1501,1522]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FC42EA9DFB99FA29" bold="true" box="[1018,1071,1500,1521]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">77-84</emphasis>
): (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FF02EAB2FF59F9D0" bold="true" box="[186,239,1523,1544]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">76-77</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FEDBEAB2FECCF9D0" bold="true" box="[355,378,1523,1544]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">78</emphasis>
) median dorsal portion of head; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FD08EAB2FD71F9D0" bold="true" box="[688,711,1523,1544]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">79</emphasis>
) median portion of pronotum; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FC54EAB2FBB5F9D0" bold="true" box="[1004,1027,1523,1544]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">80</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FE8BE948FEFCF9C6" bold="true" box="[307,330,1545,1566]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">81</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FDAFE948FDFAF9C6" bold="true" box="[535,588,1545,1566]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">82-83</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1DFF84FC58E948FC41F9C6" bold="true" box="[992,1015,1545,1566]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1162">84</emphasis>
) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1EFF87FF0AEE7AFCCEFEB6" blockId="30.[178,1085,315,366]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Abdomen narrower than elytra; punctation fine and very dense; interstices with shallow microreticulation; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1EFF87FF0AEE3CFEF9FDFD" blockId="30.[178,1086,381,549]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">
♂: sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1EFF87FED8EE3CFE1BFE4B" box="[352,429,381,403]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, posterior margin with shallow median excision, this excision with a comb of 20-25 moderately long palisade setae; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1EFF87FF02EEF9FEB1FE16" box="[186,263,440,462]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse and with unmodified pubescence, posterior incision small and broadly V-shaped; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A1EFF87FD9CEE94FD2CFE33" box="[548,666,469,491]" captionStart="Figs 76-84" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[182,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-1@29.[178,1091,212,1480]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 76-84: Lithocharis preangerana CAMERON, holotype (76), and L. parvincisa nov.sp. (77-84): (76-77) forebody; (78) median dorsal portion of head; (79) median portion of pronotum; (80) male sternite VII; (81) male sternite VIII; (82-83) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (84) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 76-77: 1.0 mm; 78-84: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184208/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Figs 82-84</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A1EFF87FCF7EE94FC14FE32" box="[847,930,469,490]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
long, without dorso-lateral apophyses; ventral process apically deeply bifid; internal structures of distinctive shapes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A1EFF87FF0AED74FCE3FD22" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1EFF87FF0AED74FCE3FD22" blockId="30.[178,1086,565,762]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">
Comparative notes: Regarding its external and male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A1EFF87FB90ED74FEABFDB0" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvincisa">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1EFF87FB90ED74FEABFDB0" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">L. parvincisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A1EFF87FD8CED12FDCFFDBF" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" box="[564,633,594,616]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilis">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A1EFF87FD8CED12FDCFFDBF" box="[564,633,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">L. vilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished by the shape of the pronotum, the more slender antennae, the less distinctly dilated protarsomeres I-IV, the shorter comb of palisade setae at the posterior margin of the male sternite VII, the less transverse male sternite VIII with a much smaller posterior excision and with unmodified pubescence, and by the smaller aedeagus without dorso-lateral apophyses and with smaller sclerotized internal structures of different shapes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B8883A1EFF87FF0AEC4BFE4AFCAF" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A1EFF87FF0AEC4BFE4AFCAF" blockId="30.[178,1085,778,888]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A1EFF87FCEEEC4BFCCCFCC7" box="[854,890,778,799]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in Dumoga-Bone National Park in 
<collectingRegion id="49FC25E13A1EFF87FD09EC66FCE3FCE4" box="[689,853,807,829]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Sulawesi Utara</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F32FAB933A1EFF87FCD4EC66FC62FCE5" box="[876,980,807,829]" name="Indonesia" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
: northern 
<collectingRegion id="49FC25E13A1EFF87FF0AEC05FEB9FC82" box="[178,271,836,858]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
) with traps baited with human faeces, with light traps, Malaise traps, and pitfall traps at altitudes of 
<quantity id="4CC046E63A1EFF87FEC2EC23FE41FCAF" box="[378,503,866,887]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="11.4" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="1163" unit="m" value="670.0" valueMax="1140.0" valueMin="200.0">200-1140 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
